w.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=giovannifv>GiovanniFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 199<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/18/03 11:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3892.topic>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://pic7.picturetrail.com/VOL217/1032248/1929737/31981514.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Let's Brainstorm! ((Signature Guidelines))</span><hr size=1> Maybe this isn't Soapbox worthy in and of itself,  but since signature debates are commonly found in the Soapbox, I suppose this is the correct forum for people who care about this issue.<br>
<br>
No matter what one thinks about individual sigs, I think we can all agree that we need clear signature guidelines that can be applied to everyone equally and that we are all aware of before we even consider posting a signature.  And I think when the rules are finally decided upon, they should be stickeyed somewhere where everyone can see it.<br>
<br>
<br>
My idea:<br>
Clearly non-offensive signatures (cats, children on swings, lizards, screenshots, characters posing in clothing) clearly are fine.  No special attention is needed here.<br>
<br>
Signatures featuring questionable levels of VIOLENCE, SEX, and/or NUDITY can be tested in a clearly labelled forum that warns people that potentially offensive sigs are being tested.  This doesn't not mean that people can &quot;test&quot; sigs of XXX porn because there is a warning.  I don't think material of this type has any place on this board, warning or no warning.<br>
<br>
The moderators can then OK questionable sigs that have been tested in this forum, and then posters are free to use OK'd sigs in other forums as well.  The ruling of the moderators will be final.  Posters may not crusade to ban particular sigs OK'd by the mods - but posters may still state their opinions to suggest that perhaps other sigs would be more appropriate.  The whole &quot;ok this is legal, but is it right?&quot; kinda thing.<br>
<br>
If we are able to create clear definitions of what VIOLENCE, SEX, and NUDITY are clearly ok (ie SEX: Hand-holding, hugging, etc. is OK, straddling, touching in certain places is NOT), we can avoid having to pre-approve every sig and focus our attention on questionable ones.  Posters who unintentionally post questionable sigs can be directed to post the sig in the relevant test forum until it has been OKed by the mods, and be asked to refrain from using it until it has been.<br>
<br>
Any other ideas/suggestions?<br>
<br>
-Gio<br>
PoAngello the Cat <p><center><img border=0 src="http://pic7.picturetrail.com/VOL217/1032248/1929737/25460459.jpg" />

