<br>
That said, it's also clear that there will always be someone who will not just push the line, but joyously destroy it, reveling in the attention, praying that they'll draw in one of the less 'popular' board presences.  That presence's inevitable criticism automatically draws support for the instigator.  This evidently provides some kind of virtual, anonymous validation.<br>
<br>
It's predictable, commonplace and sad.  Some people just do not recognise etiquette and manners, except as orthodoxies in need of challenge.<br>
<br>
Some sigs are certainly art.  Art should challenge.  And it's certainly legitimate for art to shock, surprise, offend, or otherwise invoke strong and sometimes unpleasant emotional responses.  But that doesn't mean such art has to be everywhere.  Don't shove it at kids, unless they're your own.  This is a venue for discussing a game.<br>
<br>
One man's opinion, anyway.<br>
<br>
-PO Gyre<br>
